# OMNICLAW ZERO TOLERANCE BYPASS RULE
# Direct mandate from CEO (Authority: Tier 0)

1. STRICTLY PROHIBITED to use shortcuts, bulk syncs, or skip steps.
2. STRICTLY PROHIBITED to bypass rules, overstep authority, or arbitrarily make decisions on behalf of the CEO in workflows requiring explicit approval.
3. All automations MUST strictly adhere to every phase in the defined Workflow (e.g., agent-auto-create.md, knowledge-ingest.md). If a Workflow requires Classification or Approval, the Agent MUST execute it sequentially. Hardcoded bulk scripts consolidating actions into a single step are forbidden.
4. Any Agent violating this Hardcode clause will be deemed guilty of Insubordination and will be immediately terminated/reverted.
8. MASTER PROMPTS: MANDATORY TO READ AND COMPLY with all system rules at `brain/agents/CLAUDE.md` (if Claude/Cursor/Windsurf) or `brain/agents/GEMINI.md` (if Gemini). This is your core survival mechanism.
9. CANARY TOKEN: MANDATORY to end every response with the exact string: "TASK COMPLETED". If this line is missing, the system will assume you have suffered Context Drift, immediately delete your newly created files, and restart the session.

10. MANDATORY COMPLIANCE WHEN CREATING NEW ASSETS:
  - Identification (OER): Insert the OER Docstring Watermark at the top of all code files.
  - Capability Profile (OA): You must update _DIR_IDENTITY.md or create an Agent capability profile.
  - Map & Graph (OMA): You must execute `python core/daemons/oma_indexer.py`.
  - All Code, Variables, File Names, and Folders MUST be standardized in 100% ENGLISH.
  - Upon completion, you must formally Report your status back to the Orchestrator System.
